,"meanings":["Dutch: occupational name for a cobbler.","Slovenian: nickname for a talkative person, from <i>lapati</i> ‘to babble’, or a topographic name from dialect <i>lap</i> ‘abyss’. Compare   Lapp   4."],"variants":[{"name":"Lapp","meanings":["German, English, and Dutch: from Middle High German and Middle English <i>lappe</i>, Middle Dutch <i>lap</i> ‘cloth, patch, rag’, a metonymic occupational name for a mender of clothes or shoes, or a nickname given to someone who wore ragged clothes or garments with loose folds, flaps, or hanging sleeves, or who had fleshy folds of skin on his face, neck, or body.","German: nickname for a simple-minded person, from Middle Low German <i>lappe</i> ‘fool’. This surname (in any of the two possible senses; see also 1 above) is also found in France (mainly Alsace, also Lorraine).","English: nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>lappe</i> ‘burdock’, perhaps for someone with a prickly character."]}]},{"name":"Mredydd","type":"LAST","meanings":["This is said to be the same name as Meriadek or Meiradwg, and also as the] Irish name O'Muireadwg, and the Scotch Mac Muireadaigh and Muir- eadhach. O'Reilly, however, renders the Irish word muireadach 'a sovereign, a lord j also a man's name, Morogh.' It means rather l admiral,' literally protector of the sea; from muir the sea, eadhach protector. I derive the British name from mawreddwg, mawreddig, magnificent, great, from mawr, great."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Goch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Polish Pawel, Zuzanna, Zygmunt.","North German: habitational name from any of various minor places which get their names from an ancient Germanic element <i>goch</i>, <i>gog</i> ‘marsh, bog, fen’.","Polish: from a pet form of various personal names beginning with <i>Go-</i>, such as <i>Gościsław</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Gotch","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>coch</i>, <i>goch</i> ‘red(-haired)’; see   Gooch   3.","English (Northamptonshire): variant of   Gooch   1 and 2.","Americanized form of German <b>Götsch</b> (see   Gotsch  )."]}]},{"name":"Vychan","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Welsh: A Welsh name of great antiquity, from vyckan, little, small; i.e. small in stature. Compare the surname Bychan and the Armoric Le Bihan."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrddydd Vychan ap Mredydd Goch was born about 1160, in Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the son of Mredydd Goch ap Gruffydd. He had at least 1 son with Nest Verch Ap Ifor Bach Gruffud. He died in Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1160–":"umbes 1160–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1174–Male":"1174–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","ABT 1174":"umbes 1174","about 1160":"umbes 1160","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","Presteigne, Radnor,, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Presteigne, Llythyfnwg, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1160–":"noin 1160–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1174–Male":"1174–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","ABT 1174":"noin 1174","about 1160":"noin 1160","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","Presteigne, Radnor,, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Presteigne, Llythyfnwg, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1160–":"environ 1160–Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1174–Male":"1174–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","ABT 1174":"environ 1174","about 1160":"environ 1160","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","Presteigne, Radnor,, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Wales":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Presteigne, Llythyfnwg, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrddydd Vychan ap Mredydd Goch est né en